definition.value: Catalysis of the reaction -  2 ferrocytochrome c + hydrogen peroxide -eq- 2 ferricytochrome c + 2 H2O.
Catalysis of the reaction -  cytosine + H2O -eq- uracil + NH3.
Catalysis of the reaction -  dCMP + H2O -eq- dUMP + NH3.
Catalysis of the cleavage of branch points in branched glycogen polymers.
Catalysis of the transfer of a segment of a (1--gt-4)-alpha-D-glucan to a new 4-position in an acceptor, which may be glucose or (1--gt-4)-alpha-D-glucan.

Catalysis of the hydrolysis of (1--gt-6)-alpha-D-glucosidic branch linkages in glycogen phosphorylase limit dextrin. Limit dextrin is the highly branched core that remains after exhaustive treatment of glycogen with glycogen phosphorylase. It is formed because these enzymes cannot hydrolyze the (1--gt-6) glycosidic linkages present.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2'-deoxyadenosine + ATP -eq- ADP + dAMP + 2 H(+).
Catalysis of the reaction -  NTP + deoxycytidine -eq- NDP + CMP.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2'-deoxyguanosine + ATP -eq- ADP + dGMP + 2 H(+).
Catalysis of the reaction -  2-deoxy-D-ribose 5-phosphate -eq- D-glyceraldehyde 3-phosphate + acetaldehyde.
Catalysis of the reaction -  3'-dephospho-CoA + ATP -eq- ADP + CoA + 2 H(+).
Catalysis of the reaction -  7,8-diaminononanoate + ATP + CO(2) -eq- ADP + dethiobiotin + 4 H(+) + phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  CDP-choline + 1,2-diacylglycerol -eq- CMP + a phosphatidylcholine.
Catalysis of the reaction -  NTP + 1,2-diacylglycerol -eq- NDP + 1,2-diacylglycerol-3-phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  acyl-CoA + 1,2-diacylglycerol -eq- CoA + triacylglycerol.
Catalysis of the reaction -  acetyl-CoA + an alkane-alpha,omega-diamine -eq- CoA + an N-acetyldiamine.
Catalysis of the reaction -  5,6,7,8-tetrahydrofolate + NADP+ -eq- 7,8-dihydrofolate + NADPH + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  acyl-CoA + dihydrolipoamide -eq- CoA + S-acyldihydrolipoamide, where the acyl group is a branched chain.
Catalysis of the reaction -  protein N6-(dihydrolipoyl)lysine + NAD+ -eq- protein N6-(lipoyl)lysine + NADH + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  succinyl-CoA + dihydrolipoamide -eq- CoA + S-succinyldihydrolipoamide.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2-amino-4-hydroxy-6-(D-erythro-1,2,3-trihydroxypropyl)-7,8-dihydropteridine -eq- 2-amino-4-hydroxy-6-hydroxymethyl-7,8-dihydropteridine + glycolaldehyde.
Catalysis of the reaction -  (S)-dihydroorotate + H(2)O -eq- N-carbamoyl-L-aspartate + H(+).
Catalysis of the reaction -  (S)-dihydroorotate + A -eq- AH(2) + orotate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  7,8-dihydropterin + H2O -eq- 7,8-dihydrolumazine + NH3.
Catalysis of the reaction -  a 7,8-dihydropteridine + O2 -eq- a pterin + hydrogen peroxide.
Catalysis of the reaction -  NADP+ + 5,6,7,8-tetrahydropteridine -eq- NADPH + H+ + 6,7-dihydropteridine.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2-amino-4-hydroxy-6-hydroxymethyl-7,8-dihydropteridine diphosphate + 4-aminobenzoate -eq- diphosphate + dihydropteroate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  5,6-dihydrouracil + H2O -eq- 3-ureidopropionate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  (S)-dihydroorotate + O(2) -eq- H(2)O(2) + orotate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  5,6-dihydrouracil + NAD+ -eq- uracil + NADH + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2,3-dihydroxy-3-methylbutanoate -eq- 3-methyl-2-oxobutanoate + H2O.
Catalysis of the reaction -  dimethylallyl diphosphate + isopentenyl diphosphate -eq- diphosphate + geranyl diphosphate.
Catalysis of the removal of a methyl group from N-nitrosodimethylamine.
Catalysis of the reaction -  (R)-5-diphosphomevalonate + ATP -eq- ADP + CO(2) + H(+) + isopentenyl diphosphate + phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  S-adenosyl-L-methionine + 2-(3-carboxy-3-aminopropyl)-L-histidine -eq- S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + 2-(3-carboxy-3-(methylammonio)propyl)-L-histidine.
Catalysis of the reaction -  3-cis-dodecenoyl-CoA -eq- 2-trans-dodecenoyl-CoA.
Catalysis of the reaction -  UDP-N-acetyl-D-glucosamine + dolichyl phosphate -eq- UDP + dolichyl N-acetyl-alpha-D-glucosaminyl phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  L-dopachrome -eq- 5,6-dihydroxyindole-2-carboxylate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  CTP + dolichol -eq- CDP + dolichyl phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  dolichyl phosphate D-mannose + protein -eq- dolichyl phosphate + O-D-mannosylprotein.
Catalysis of the reaction -  dUTP + H2O -eq- dUMP + diphosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  Ecdysone + palmitoyl-CoA -eq- CoA + ecdysone palmitate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  reduced ETF + ubiquinone -eq- ETF + ubiquinol.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of internal, alpha-peptide bonds in a polypeptide chain.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + H2O -eq- ADP + phosphate, to drive the hydrolysis of peptide bonds.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of N-terminal amino acid residues from in a polypeptide chain.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of the terminal or penultimate peptide bond at the C-terminal end of a peptide or polypeptide.

Catalysis of the hydrolysis of C-terminal amino acid residues from a polypeptide chain by a mechanism in which water acts as a nucleophile, one or two metal ions hold the water molecule in place, and charged amino acid side chains are ligands for the metal ions.

Catalysis of the hydrolysis of a peptide bond not more than three residues from the C-terminus of a polypeptide chain by a catalytic mechanism that involves a catalytic triad consisting of a serine nucleophile that is activated by a proton relay involving an acidic residue (e.g. aspartate or glutamate) and a basic residue (usually histidine).

Catalysis of the hydrolysis of internal, alpha-peptide bonds in a polypeptide chain by a mechanism in which a water molecule bound by the side chains of aspartic residues at the active center acts as a nucleophile.
